{{Unreferenced|date=November 2016}}
'''Cultural retention''' is the act of retaining the [[culture]] of a specific [[ethnicity|ethnic]] group of people, especially when there is reason to believe that the culture, through inaction, may be lost. Many African-American, European and Asian organizations have cultural retention programs in place.

